        "Panoramas1": "Local Events and Celebrations",
        "Panoramas2": "The commune of Colbún is characterized by a rich cultural tradition and a vibrant calendar of activities that stand out throughout the year. These events, full of history and customs, unite the inhabitants of the commune and attract visitors from all over the country.",
        "Panoramas3": "Highlights of our upcoming events and activities",
        "Petroglyphs": "Petroglyphs",
        "PetroglyphsRemember": "The petroglyphs of Guaiquivilo are an invitation to connect with the past through a valuable and invaluable archaeological heritage. These were a form of communication of the first inhabitants of the Maule region and still resist the inexorable passage of time. In the middle of the mountains, next to a river, it will be inevitable not to think about those ancestors who took refuge for months in the place, and who still communicate with us through those drawings, inviting you to discover their meaning.",
        "PetroglifosInfo": "The petroglyphs of Guaiquivilo are located in the Cajón de Calabozos, in the middle of the foothills of El Melado. More than 900 drawings inscribed in granitic rock are distributed in a horizontal slope that faces the Guaiquivilo River, containing biomorphic, phytomorphic and zoomorphic drawings. It constitutes one of the deposits of Chile with more petroglyphs concentrated in the same place",
