        "Toba": "Toba Stone",
        "TobaInfo": "Since time immemorial, artisans have carved tufa stone using techniques reminiscent of woodworking. This skill has been passed down from generation to generation, making each piece a testament to human ingenuity and connection to the land. The stone's porosity not only lends it lightness, but also gives it remarkable strength, making it ideal for a variety of applications, from decorative elements to useful everyday objects.",
