        "ZoitZone": "ZOIT Zone",
        "ZoitText1": "The ZOIT Lake Colbún - Rari is made up of part of the communes of San Clemente and Colbún, which share in their and Colbún, which share the northern and southern shores of Lake Colbún in the Maule region. in the Maule region. After 4 years of ZOIT management, the destination for its extension will maintain the vision of will maintain the vision of: “Positioning itself as a destination for nature tourism, adventure, sports and cultural tradition, based on tourism development in the foothills of the development, focusing on Lake Colbún as the main attraction and axis of its development, together with the town of Rari; with a national and international recognition”. and international recognition”.",
        "ZoitText2": "Its mission will be: “To promote the organization of the tourist activity, allowing to go towards the overcoming of gaps and a sustainable development, rescuing the traditions of the region. to overcome gaps and sustainable development, rescuing traditions and identity to promote a destination of nature, countryside and identity to promote a destination of nature, countryside, heritage and nautical activities with a tourist nautical activities with an attractive tourist offer for national visitors”.",
        "ZoitText3": "In addition to the above, we must point out the following, a huge number of activities, fairs and cultural festivals take place in our commune annually, cultural fairs and festivals take place in our commune every year, always associated to our identity and that which most distinguishes each local community, passing through the Crin the Crin, the Loom, the carts, the Esquilas, Religious Festivals, among others, and that are Religious Festivities among others, which are nationally renowned. National Handicrafts and Folklore and Folklore Panimávida, the Fiesta de la Esquila, La noche de San Juan (the only winter festival in the region), Chan Chanel (the only winter festival in the region), Chancho al Humo, Fiesta del Crin, San Sebastian (nationally recognized (nationally recognized activity), among many others, where there is a public that normally doubles the total that normally doubles the total of the communal population.",
